pullRequest.body:
This PR is the first step to migrate from semibundled ordered algebraic typeclasses to mixin typeclasses. This will significantly reduce the number of typeclasses and improve performance. See #20676.

This PR introduces 2 typeclasses `CanonicallyOrderedAdd` `CanonicallyOrderedMul` and deprecates legacy semibundled `CanonicallyOrdered*` typeclasses.

```suggestion
instance instCanonicallyOrderedAdd [AddZeroClass α] [Preorder α] [CanonicallyOrderedAdd α] :
```
The old instance was incorrectly named, I guess.
Let's do this in a follow-up PR.
No problem if it is a pain, but if it is possible to rearrange the order of theorems here so the omit isn't necessary that would be nice.

```suggestion
  be more natural than collections of all things ≥ 1). -/
```

We might want to flip this around! Let's not do that in this PR though.

But we also see that with valuations: additive ones naturally take values in a `WithTop A`, where `A` is a linearly ordered additive comm group. But multiplicative ones naturally take values in `WithZero G`. The `WithTop` vs `WithZero` is an artifact of flipping the order when moving between the two notions.

I'm not really qualified to approve this refactor however, I don't have much experience with these sorts of large sweeping changes.
